      <div xml:id="NA183-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu varaiviṭaivaittup piriyun talaivaṟkut tōḻi colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">What the confidante said to HIM who separated after fixing the time for marriage.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA183">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            taṉṉāṭṭu viḷainta veṇṇeṟ ṟantu</l>
<l>            piṟanāṭ ṭuppiṉ koḷḷai cāṟṟi</l>
<l>            neṭuneṟi yoḻukai nilavumaṇa ṉīnti</l>
<l>            yavaṇuṟai muṉinta vokkaloṭu pulampeyarn</l>
<l>            tumaṇar pōkalu miṉṉā tāku </l>
<l>            maṭavai maṉṟamma koṇka vayiṉṟō</l>
<l>            ṟiṉṉā talaikku mūtaiyō ṭōru</l>
<l>            nummil pulampiṉ mālaiyu muṭaittē</l>
<l>            yiṉamī ṉārnta veṇkuruku mititta</l>
<l>            vaṟunīr neytal pōla </l>
<l>            vāḻā ḷātal cūḻā tōyē.</l>
            </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>When the salt-merchants are all gone(?),<note place="foot">Is inclusiveness in the sense of "altogether gone" the meaning of -<term xml:lang="ta">um</term> in <term xml:lang="ta">pōkalum</term>?</note></l>
<l rend="indent">leaving [their] soil along with [their] kinsfolk, who hated to stay there,</l>
<l rend="indent">crossing the moonlit sand on carts by small paths,</l>
<l rend="indent">announcing the price of the salt in other lands,</l>
<l rend="indent">giving [it in exchange] for white paddy, ripened in their land<note place="foot">Actually, this attribute makes only sense when connected with the salt, not with the rice.</note>,</l>
<l rend="indent4">[the place] will be unpleasant.</l>
<l>Foolish indeed, alas, [are] you, man from the sea:</l>
<l>your house has evenings of loneliness too, to which one listens(?)<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">ōrum</term> is explained as expletive here by T.V.G., and it is indeed hard to make sense of.</note>,</l>
<l rend="indent">along with the cold wind that dashes unpleasantly on all sides,</l>
<l>– you who do not consider that she won't live,</l>
<l rend="indent">as a waterlily in scanty water,</l>
<l rend="indent2">trampled by white egrets that have fed on various fish.</l>
        </lg>
